    INTRODUCTION TO BROILER CHICKEN PRODUCTION

    Click to edit text

    Section colors
    Duplicate section
    Delete section

    OBJECTIVES:

    • Students will learn about broiler chicken production, including brooding, feeding, and proper care for healthy growth. 


    Click to edit text

    Section colors
    Duplicate section
    Delete section

    Broiler chicken production is a method of raising chickens for meat. The key factors in raising healthy broilers include proper brooding (temperature control, clean environment), balanced feeding, vaccination, and regular monitoring of growth and health. 

    Click to edit text

    Section colors
    Duplicate section
    Delete section

    This chart shows the three main growth stages of broiler chickens: Brooding (Day 17), Growth (Day 821), and Finishing (Day 2235). It includes the recommended temperature for each stage and the key activities needed to ensure healthy development, such as feeding, monitoring, and preparing for harvest. 


    Click to edit text

    Section colors
    Duplicate section
    Delete section

    This diagram illustrates the step-by-step process of caring for broiler chickens. It shows how to set up the brooding cage with a heat source, feeders, and waterers, distribute chicks evenly, feed them properly, monitor their health, gradually reduce heat, and provide balanced feed and water until they are ready for harvest.

    What is the ideal temperature for brooding chicks?

    a) 25C

    b) 3235C 

    c) 40C

    Which system is commonly used for raising broilers?

    a) Free-range

    b) Deep Litter System 

    c) Battery Cage

    True or False: Chicks should be vaccinated to prevent diseases. 

    What is FCR (Feed Conversion Ratio)?

    a) Amount of feed per chicken

    b) Ratio of feed intake to weight gain 

    c) Amount of water given

    Instructions:
